# Git already stores every text file LF-only. Without this, core.autocrlf=true
# checks them out CRLF on Windows, which Biome (formatter.lineEnding defaults to
# "lf") then reports as a formatting error in every file — `pnpm lint` fails on a
# clean Windows checkout. Pin the working tree to LF on every platform so the
# checkout matches what Git and Biome both expect.
* text=auto eol=lf
